Description: This registry defines messages for representing SyncAgent errors in Redfish

ADLDAPPatchError.Description: The AD and LDAP Patch has been failed
ADLDAPPatchError.Message: The AD and LDAP Patch has been failed
ADLDAPPatchError.Resolution: Please provide valid data and try again.

ADPatchError.Description: The AD Patch has been failed
ADPatchError.Message: The AD Patch has been failed
ADPatchError.Resolution: Please provide valid data and try again.

ADRolePatchError.Description: Patching AD Role has been failed
ADRolePatchError.Message: Patching AD Role has been failed
ADRolePatchError.Resolution: Please provide valid data and try again.

AddressDuplicatedInRequest.Description: IPv6 address already exists in request body
AddressDuplicatedInRequest.Message: IPv6 address %1 is duplicated in request body
AddressDuplicatedInRequest.Resolution: Provide unique IPv6 Address for each IPv6 indexes

AddressOrigin.Description: Indicates that address origin is tried for patch.
AddressOrigin.Resolution: Try patch for IPv4 properties other than address origin

AddressOriginStatic.Description: Indicates that AddressOrigin is patched with other patchable properties.
AddressOriginStatic.Message: AddressOrigin is patched with other patchable properties.
AddressOriginStatic.Resolution: Try giving patch request removing AddressOrigin property

AutoNegEnabled.Description: Indicates patch is applied for auto negotiation where mode is not supported
AutoNegEnabled.Message: Cannot apply patch auto-negotiation for this interface
AutoNegEnabled.Resolution: Enable auto negotiation mode and apply patch for auto-neg

AutoNegFalse.Description: Indicates that a patch is tried to set autoneg value to false without other required properties.
AutoNegFalse.Message: Required all AutoNeg, SpeedMbps and FullDuplex values to set AutoNeg to false
AutoNegFalse.Resolution: Sent patch filling AutoNeg, SpeedMbps and FullDuplex values to set AutoNeg to false

AutoNegTrue.Description: Indicates that a patch is tried with all AutoNeg, SpeedMbps and FullDuplex values to set autoneg to true.
AutoNegTrue.Message: Required only AutoNeg value to set AutoNeg to true
AutoNegTrue.Resolution: Sent patch only with AutoNeg values to set AutoNeg to true

AutoNegWithOtherProperties.Description: Indicates that a patch is tried with other allowed properties without autoneg value.
AutoNegWithOtherProperties.Message: Required AutoNeg values to make any changes in negotiation values
AutoNegWithOtherProperties.Resolution: Sent patch filling AutoNeg values to make any changes in negotiation values

BondEnabled.Description: Indicates that bond is enabled so patch cannot be tried for other interfaces.
BondEnabled.Message: Bond is enabled, Patch is not applicable for this interface
BondEnabled.Resolution: Disable bond and apply patch for the interface

BondEnabledAutoNeg.Description: Indicates that bond is enabled so we cannot change auto-neg values.
BondEnabledAutoNeg.Message: AutoNeg values cannot be changed when bond is enabled
BondEnabledAutoNeg.Resolution: Disable Bond and after enabling eth0/eth1 try changing auto-neg values for the enabled interface

ClearAllAddress.Resolution: Do not clear All of the IPv6Addresses

DHCPEnabled.Description: Indicates that DHCPv4 is enabled on the interface.
DHCPEnabled.Message: DHCPv4 is enabled on the interface
DHCPEnabled.Resolution: Disable DHCP to perform this operation

DHCPv6Enabled.Description: Indicates that DHCPv4 is enabled on the interface.
DHCPv6Enabled.Message: DHCPv6 is enabled on the interface
DHCPv6Enabled.Resolution: Disable DHCP to perform this operation

DeleteTimeout.Description: Indicates that the property was not changed or did not cause an error before a timeout occurred.
DeleteTimeout.Message: The timeout duration (%1s) was exceeded before the delete operation on %2 responded.
DeleteTimeout.Resolution: Verify the request is valid and resubmit the request if necessary.

DisableDHCPv4.Description: Provide ipv4 static address to disable dhcpv4
DisableDHCPv4.Message: To disable DHCPv4 provide %1 property along with DHCPEnabled
DisableDHCPv4.Resolution: Provide mandatory properties while disabling dhcpv4

DisableDHCPv6.Description: Provide ipv6 static address to disable dhcpv6
DisableDHCPv6.Message: To disable DHCPv6 provide %1 property along with OperatingMode
DisableDHCPv6.Resolution: Provide mandatory properties while disabling dhcpv6

EjectMediaError.Message: EjectMedia action is unsuccessful. IPMI Error code: %1
EjectMediaError.Resolution: Please make sure all the required features are enabled and the given media instance in the URI is valid

EnableAD.Description: Enable Active Directory authentication before creating role
EnableAD.Message: Role can be created only if Active Directory authentication is enabled
EnableAD.Resolution: Provide Active Directory authentication before creating role

EnableDHCP.Description: Provide only dhcpv6/v4 enabled property alone
EnableDHCP.Message: dhcpv6/v4-enabled property is applied along with ipv6/ipv4 values while enabling dhcp
EnableDHCP.Resolution: Provide dhcpv6/v4-enabled property alone while enabling dhcp for ipv6/ipv4

EnableLDAP.Description: Enable LDAP authentication before creating role
EnableLDAP.Message: Role can be created only if LDAP authentication is enabled
EnableLDAP.Resolution: Provide LDAP authentication before creating role

ExceedLimit.Description: Indicates applied patch value not within limit
ExceedLimit.Message: Applied patch value not within limit

FQDNHostName.Description: Indicates that FQDN and HostName are not same.
FQDNHostName.Resolution: FQDN and HostName should be same

IDOutOfRange.Description: Group ID value provided not supported
IDOutOfRange.Message: Group ID value %2 is out of range
IDOutOfRange.Resolution: Provide valid Group Id value within range of 1 to 5

IPAddressValueOutOfRange.Message: IPAddress or Gateway value is out of range
IPAddressValueOutOfRange.Resolution: Provide valid IPAddress or Gateway value within the range

IPMISOLReadOnlyProperty.Description: Indicates that the serial interface property is defined by IPMI Serial-Over-LAN spec and is therefore read-only.
IPMISOLReadOnlyProperty.Message: %1 is a property of an IPMI Serial-Over-LAN interface and is defined to be read-only.
IPMISOLReadOnlyProperty.Resolution: Remove the property from the request and resubmit the request if necessary.

IPv4Disabled.Message: IPv4 is disabled for the interface
IPv4Disabled.Resolution: Enabled IPv4 for the interface and apply the patch

IPv6Both.Description: Indicates patch is applied for both ipv6addresses and ipv6staticaddress at same time
IPv6Both.Message: Cannot try both the property (IPv6Addresses or Ipv6StaticAddress) in a single patch

IPv6Disabled.Message: IPv6 is disabled for the interface
IPv6Disabled.Resolution: Enabled IPv6 for the interface and apply the patch

InsertMediaError.Resolution: Please make sure all the required features are enabled, provided data are valid and try again.

InterfaceDisabled.Description: Indicates that the interface for given patch is disabled.
InterfaceDisabled.Message: The interface for given patch is disabled

InterfaceEnabledBondEnabled.Description: Indicates InterfaceEnabled property cannot be applied in patch for eth0/eth1 interface when bond is enabled.
InterfaceEnabledBondEnabled.Message: InterfaceEnabled property patch cannot be applied for eth0/eth1 instance if bond is enabled
InterfaceEnabledBondEnabled.Resolution: Remove the property from the request body and resubmit the request if the operation failed

InterfaceEnabledBondInterface.Description: Indicates InterfaceEnabled property cannot be applied in patch for bond0 interface.
InterfaceEnabledBondInterface.Message: InterfaceEnabled property is read-only for bond0 interface.
InterfaceEnabledBondInterface.Resolution: InterfaceEnabled property can be applied only for eth0 or eth1 instance

LDAPPatchError.Description: The LDAP Patch has been failed
LDAPPatchError.Message: The LDAP Patch has been failed
LDAPPatchError.Resolution: Please provide valid data and try again.

LDAPRolePatchError.Description: Patching LDAP Role has been failed
LDAPRolePatchError.Message: Patching LDAP Role has been failed
LDAPRolePatchError.Resolution: Please provide valid data and try again.

MACAddress.Message: Patching MACAddress or PermanentMACAddress not allowed

MinimumNameServerRequired.Description: Indicates that all three name servers values not provided
MinimumNameServerRequired.Message: All three nameservers are provided with null values
MinimumNameServerRequired.Resolution: Minimum one nameserver value needs to be provided

MultipleArray.Description: Indicates patch is applied with multiple sets
MultipleArray.Message: Cannot apply patch with multiple sets, patch is supported for only single set

NCSIEnabled.Description: Indicates that a property was given a value in the request body, but the property is not supported due to NCSI Port.
NCSIEnabled.Message: NCSI support is enabled for the interface. Configuring %1, %2 and %3 is forbidden
NCSIEnabled.Resolution: AutoNeg, SpeedMbps and FullDuplex are not writable due to NCSI Port

NoBondSingleInterface.Description: Indicates that only one interface is enabled so we cannot enable bond
NoBondSingleInterface.Message: Only one of the ethernet interface is enabled, Cannot enable bond with single interface
NoBondSingleInterface.Resolution: Both eth0 and eth1 should be up to enable bond

OnePropertyAtATime.Description: Indicates patch cannot be applied for the given properties at same time
OnePropertyAtATime.Message: Value %1 for the property %2 cannot be applied when %3 is given in the request body
OnePropertyAtATime.Resolution: Remove one property and resubmit the request

PartialPatch.Description: Indicates that a property was given a value in the request body, but the property is not implemented as a writable property.
PartialPatch.Message: Apart from read only properties, other properties are successful
PartialPatch.Resolution: Try giving get request to see the changes for the successful patch

PatchFormat.Description: Patch body format is not correct
PatchFormat.Message: Patch body format is not correct
PatchFormat.Resolution: Apply patch body in correct format

PatchIPMIError.Description: Indicates that the operation failed since IPMI function return error.
PatchIPMIError.Message: The Patch operation has been failed for %1
PatchIPMIError.Resolution: Please provide valid data and try again.

PatchInProgress.Description: Indicates that the previous patch is in progress
PatchInProgress.Resolution: Try applying new patch after the previous process is completed

PatchNotSupported.Description: Indicates that the selected interface cannot be disabled due to NCSI support enabled.
PatchNotSupported.Message: NCSI support is enabled for the interface %1, the interface cannot be disabled
PatchNotSupported.Resolution: Property is not writable due to NCSI support enabled and patch not supported for this property

PatchTimeout.Description: Indicates that the property was not changed or did not cause an error before a timeout occurred.
PatchTimeout.Message: The timeout duration (%1s) was exceeded before the patch operation on %2 responded.
PatchTimeout.Resolution: Resource is taking more than the configured timeout seconds to respond. Please verify if the request is valid or check if the operation was successful using GET operation on the URI/resource. Resubmit the request if necessary.

PatchValueAlreadyExists.Message: Cannot patch the value which already applied
PatchValueAlreadyExists.Resolution: Provide other supported value then try patch again

PostTimeout.Description: Indicates that the property was not changed or did not cause an error before a timeout occurred.
PostTimeout.Message: The timeout duration (%1s) was exceeded before the post operation on %2 responded.
PostTimeout.Resolution: Verify the request is valid and resubmit the request if necessary.

PrefixLength.Resolution: Provide correct patch body without prefixlength

PropertyModificationNotImplemented.Description: Indicates that a property was given a value in the request body, but the property is not implemented as a writable property.
PropertyModificationNotImplemented.Message: Modifying property %1 is not possible in the current implementation and cannot be assigned a value.
PropertyModificationNotImplemented.Resolution: Remove the property from the request body and resubmit the request if the operation failed.

PropertyNotConfigurable.Description: Indicates that the requested write of a property value could not be completed, due to the current state.
PropertyNotConfigurable.Message: Modifying property %1 is not possible in the current configuration state and cannot be assigned a value.
PropertyNotConfigurable.Resolution: Remove property from payload and resubmit or make sure the service supports configuration and resubmit with the same payload

ProvideServiceEnabled.Resolution: Provide both ServiceEnabled and Authentication property

RelatedPropertyMissingorInvalid.Description: Indicates that the operation failed since some related properties were missing or is invalid
RelatedPropertyMissingorInvalid.Message: To set the value %1 to the property %2, the required property %3 is absent or is invalid in the request data
RelatedPropertyMissingorInvalid.Resolution: Give all the valid inputs and resubmit the request

SameIPv6Address.Message: Provided IPv6 address %1 in request already exists in index %2
SameIPv6Address.Resolution: Provide IPv6 address which is not already available

SameInterfaceEnabledState.Description: Indicates that same value is given for InterfaceEnabled property to patch.
SameInterfaceEnabledState.Message: Trying to patch already set value for interface state
SameInterfaceEnabledState.Resolution: Change patch value other than already available value for Interface state

SingleEthernetEnabled.Description: Indicates that only one interface is enabled so we cannot disable both the ethernet interface.
SingleEthernetEnabled.Message: Only one of the ethernet interface is enabled, Cannot disable both the ethernet interface
SingleEthernetEnabled.Resolution: Minimum one of available ethernet interface should be enabled

SinglePortEnabled.Description: Indicates that the single port app feature prevented the action from being processed normally.
SinglePortEnabled.Message: %1 cannot be changed when the single port app feature is enabled.
SinglePortEnabled.Resolution: Disable single port app feature and resubmit the request.

SpeedMbpsValueNotInList.Description: SpeedMbps value not supported for AutoNeg value false
SpeedMbpsValueNotInList.Message: SpeedMbps value not supported for AutoNeg false

StaticIPnotAssigned.Description: Indicates that the selected index does not have ip assigned
StaticIPnotAssigned.Message: The selected one or more index does not have ip assigned to be cleared
StaticIPnotAssigned.Resolution: Try index where ip is assigned

StaticIndexExist.Message: Provided IPv6 Static Index in request already exits
StaticIndexExist.Resolution: Provide IPv6 Static Index which is not exist

TimeoutError.Description: Indicates that the property was not changed or did not cause an error before a timeout occurred.
TimeoutError.Message: The timeout duration (%1s) was exceeded before the operation on %2 responded.
TimeoutError.Resolution: Resource is taking more than 15 seconds to respond. Please verify if the request is valid or check if the operation was successful using GET operation on the URI/resource. Resubmit the request if necessary.

UnspecifiedError.Description: Indicates that the attempt to update the property resulted in an error with and undetermined cause.
UnspecifiedError.Message: An unspecified error occurred while fulfilling the request, the value of %1 may have changed.
UnspecifiedError.Resolution: Verify the state of the resource and resubmit the request if necessary.

VLANIdOutOfRange.Message: VLANId value %2 is out of range
VLANIdOutOfRange.Resolution: Provide valid VLANId value within range of 2 to 4094

ValueNotSupported.Description: Indicates that the property was not changed because the value given was not supported by the backend implementation.
ValueNotSupported.Message: The value '%1' for property %2 is not supported by the backend implementation for this resource.
ValueNotSupported.Resolution: Verify the request is valid and resubmit the request if necessary.

WaitTime.Description: Updating attributes, please try after some time
WaitTime.Message: Attributes are updating, kindly try after 30 seconds

requestset.Description: Indicates patch is applied for different sets
requestset.Message: Cannot apply patch for different sets
requestset.Resolution: Provide valid sets for patch {IPv4StaticAddresses, IPv6StaticAddresses, VLAN, InterfaceEnabled}, {FQDN, HostName}, {AutoNeg, SpeedMbps, FullDuplex, MTUSize}

Name: SyncAgent Message Registry
